rComments: Worst Biochem class I've taken. The class itself is not hard but he does not explain the material well. Doesn't care about his students, barely replies to emails AND you can drop from A- to a B due to the SMALLEST misunderstanding (which is what happened to me). Never taking him again... I was so looking forward to this class but now I hate it.

Horrible teacher. Makes you take all the notes in class so you cant listen. Talks super slowly and boring. If you cant attend class for some reasons, dont bother emailing him for notes or help he will ignore you.
Dont reply to email if he doesnt like you horrible teacher. Doesn't care about his student and dont care about helping them.
super condescending and does not care about his students at all. his TA is very rough with the corrections for assignments.
Good lecture, no exams during COVID, just assignments that are applied questions -- pick an enzyme and show me these qualities of it.

He is looking for specific answers in his exams so you have to learn everything by heart but the lectures are interesting and you can see he is passionate about what he teaches. Would recommend this class with this prof
Condescending, does not respond to emails, not welcoming during office hours.

Très condescendant et a une mauvaise attitude. Lorsqu'il n'aime pas l'étudiant n'hésite pas à le montrer en pressant l'étudiant afin qu'il pose le moins de questions possibles et ce que ce soit en classe ou à son bureau. Ne prend pas la peine de répondre à ses messages. Montre clairement son dédain pour l'étudiant en question! Injuste et désagréabl

AMAZING PROF! Crystal clear handwritten notes. Sadly, the examples given in class are nowhere near as difficult as the ones in the midterm, which is a shame. Material is very difficult, although he tries to help. First midterm is fair, second midterm made me cry. Exam had a bit of everything which is good. Study the labs, they are on the exam!!
Good prof, explains very well. Test are difficult and harshly graded.
En général, il est un bon prof et ses notes sont très claires mais la matière elle-même est assez difficile.

Loved this prof! Best prof I've had thus far. When he teaches, everything is extremely clear. The exercises he hands out are really helpful and reflect what is on the tests so there are no surprises. I also enjoy that there's always a bonus question on each test :) Also, I didn't buy the textbook and I didn't need it.

There was no surprises in the midterms, almost all questions were picked from the (optionnal) homeworks, so be sure to do those. Overall, he explains well, all of the notes are taken by hand so it's not too fast paced. Great prof.

He's an amazing prof and explains the material really well. He's also very nice, approachable, and helpful. He clearly cares for his students. His notes are handwritten and he explains while writing them down which makes skipping class impossible if you're wanting a relatively good grade. Exams reflect well the material but are still challenging.

Mid terms are relatively fair if you complete all the homework however the exam, although suppose to accumulative, mostly only included materiel from the last 2 units... Would not recommend this prof.
All notes are taken by hand. He doesn't go too fast because he's writing it out too which is fantastic! Tests were fair. Great intro to organic chem!
amazing prof. loved everything about this course. would do it all over again.

Notes are really clear, however examples given in class are really easy compared to actual problems. For the final exam used a lot of questions from homework. Very picky. But not a bad prof. Sometimes doesn't teach the concepts well. DGD are useless. Overall decent prof.
Possible the most condescending professor and the least understanding.

Not enough examples, not all the solutions to the homework were posted online, he made it seem like the DGD was mandatory because those homework questions which weren't answered "would be answered in the DGD's" which they weren't, the DGD's were not helpful at all, when asked if he could give us a practice exam, he said he "didn't have any".
I hear from other that he can be hard, but really good in organic chemistry. If you can only take organic chemistry in French, just go to class and do recommend exercise.
Love him. Amazing prof, makes organic chemistry interesting and easy! Listen in class and do the assignments.
great prof! made organic chemistry easy. easy to follow in class, highly recommended
By far the best techer I ever had, he made me love organic chemistry, makes everything that looks scary very clear and quite easy. Very nice person also! Take this class with him it is a must.
amazing, just amazing! he's clear and straight to the point! he's TA's make a lot of mistakes when correcting midterms/final so watch out!!
Ce prof est le meilleur prof que j'ai jamais eu. Il explique vraiment bien, il est sympathique et il tient à la réussite de ses élèves. Il rend la chimie organique amusante.

Easily the best prof in my first year. The textbook use is low but have good practice and examples for extra. You can also find some of the lab theory in the manual. CLean notes, very helpful during his office hours (the ones right before the exam).
Ses explications sont très claires. Je recommande ce professeur.
Loved this class! exams really fair but you still had to study to get a good grade! Always answering students questions! really makes you love chemistry!

Chica is an awesome prof! His exams are fair, homework and notes are clear. Excellent at explaining, takes his time and makes sure the concepts are clear. I never liked organic chemistry but after taking his class I found myself to like it because I understand the concepts! I recommend him, best prof by far!

Excellent prof! Takes his time explaining in various ways, very patient, very considerate, very clear in his expectations, understands that org chem isn't easy but makes it easier for us! Thanks for everything, the best. I now love org chem.
Great prof. Final  exam was very easy, easier than the midterms. Best org chem ever !
Vraiment bon enseignant! Il explique très bien et prend le temps de faire passer la matière de façon clair et précise.
One of the best professors I've had in my life... Thank you.

Although Prof. Chica assigns many homework questions from the textbook, I have never used it once. Just make sure you do all his 'devoirs', read over his notes and understand the material perfectly because it only gets harder as the course advances. Really nice and down to earth person though. Good luck!
Awesome prof. Really nice and helpful. Also, course is clear and notes are very well done. Midterms and final were really easy if you did the weekly exercies he gives. Textbook wasn't very useful.
Roberto is a very fair teacher his notes are flawless and he tells you what to expect on the exam. Much better than Alyson Flynn who teaches the english section. Overall solid prof and solid class

Fantastic teacher. The best professor I had during my first year in university. His notes are extremely clear and organized. His homework assignments prepare you well for the midterms, but the final was very different and a lot harder.

Good prof. As much as I hate organic chem, Chica made it much easier to tolerate. He is clear, helpful and basically writes down notes which you copy word for word and study later. Going to class was a must for me though as it is hard to fully understand just from the notes alone. I did alright on the midterms but the final was much harder IMHO
Very nice professor. Very clear, answers questions after class, very patient and gives very useful homework that is very close to the midterms and exams.

Awesome teacher. He's very clear in his explanations and makes the course enjoyable. Don't bother doing the exercices in the book (kinda useless and hard for nothing) but do the homeworks he assigns since it reflects the midterms. He's awesome one-on-one so dont be scared to ask him questions.
